HEADWORD: Candlepin
<hw>Can`dle*pin`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Tenpins)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A form of bowling pin slender and nearly straight like
a candle.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The game played with such pins; -- in
form <altname>candlepins</altname>, used as a singular.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

